sentences: Noël Akchoté (born 7 December 1968) is a French guitarist in free improvisation, classical, experimental, and free jazz.
During the 1990s he worked with Joey Baron, Lol Coxhill,  Glenn Ferris, Daniel Humair, Michel Portal, Sam Rivers, Aldo Romano, Louis Sclavis,  and Henri Texier.
He was a member of the Recyclers, Trash Corporation, and was a founder the Big Four in 2001 with Steven Bernstein, Bradley Jones, and Max Nagl.
Big Four, with Max Nagl, Steven Bernstein, Bradley Jones (Hatology, 2002)
Goodbye Gary Cooper (Make Up, 1999)With David Grubbs
Derek Bailey, Close to the Kitchen (Rectangle, 1996)
Philippe Katerine, Nom De Code: Sacha (Rectangle, 2002)
Evan Parker, Live at Les Instants Chavires (Leo, 1998)
1999 Exhibitions (by John B. Root, with Dolly Golden, Coralie, Karen Lancaume, Élodie Chérie)
2001 Nom de Code : Sacha (short film by Thierry Jousse with Katerine, Margot Abascal, Anna Karina)
2002 XYZ (by John B. Root, with Titof, Ovidie, Ksandra, Élodie Chérie)
2004 Les Invisibles (by Thierry Jousse with Laurent Lucas, Lio, Michael Lonsdale, Margot Abascal)
Témoignages sur un holy ghost, Le Mot et le Reste, 2010.
Starting on guitar at when he was eight years old, he received lessons on classical guitar in school.
At fourteen he was performing day and night in bars and restaurants.
